Package com.pandora.config.species

package com.pandora.config.species
The com.pandora.config.species package contains classes and interfaces related to the configuration and management of biogeochemical species in the Pandora biogeochemical model. This package includes implementations of specific species, abstractions for common functionality, and services for handling species configurations.

The main components in this package are:

DOC and DIC represent specific biogeochemical species with configured properties such as name, unit, molar mass, and oxidation rate.

This package contributes to the configuration and behavior of biogeochemical species within PANDORA, supporting modular and extensible management of various species in a freshwater system.
